                <p> CFA declares the Fire Danger during period of increased fire risk.</p>
                <p> During this fire danger period permits is required who need to use fire in open.</p>
                <p> Burning of fine fuels where essential, needs a Schedule 13 permit.</p>

                <ul>
                    <li>Check with your local council, CFA District office or FRV Regional Office to obtain an application form.</li>
                </ul>

            </div>
            <button class="btn1 s14" id="s14NF">Fire Danger Period (Schedule 14) Permit</button>
            <div class="collapse txt_s14 inner" style="font-family:Roboto-light">
                <p style="text-align:justify;">If burn-off purpose is not covered above by Schedule 13 permit, Like biosecurity requirements such as diseased plants or deceased livestock, essential hot works to repair or maintain infrastructure on rail or road corridors, solid fuel catering, fireworks, blacksmithing, hot air ballooning, bird scaring device.</p>
                <h2><strong>Apply</strong></h2>

                <form target="_blank" action="@Url.Action("Schedule14","Home")">
                    <input class="fillbtn" type="submit" value="Fill the Form" /> and email to <a style="color:red" href="fire.restrictions@cfa.vic.gov.au">  fire.restrictions@cfa.vic.gov.au </a>
                </form>

                <hr />
                <div>or post to below address</div>
                <div style="text-align:left;padding-top:20px;">
                    <p>CFA Permit Officer</p>
                    <p>Level 8 136, Exhibition Street</p>
                    <p> Melbourne VIC 8002</p>
                    <hr />
                </div>


            </div>



            <button class="btn1 s40" id="s40NF">Total Fire Ban (Section 40) Permit </button>
            <div class="collapse txt_s40 inner" style="font-family:Roboto-light">
                <h2>Total Fire Ban</h2>
                <p style="text-align:justify">
                    Don't lit the fire in the open air unless you have a special permit.
                    Total fire ban is declared by the CFA when fire can spread and could be uncontrolable.
                </p>
                <h2>Total Fire Ban Permit (Section 40) Eligibility</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Community organisations</li>
                    <li> Charitable organisations</li>
                    <li>Fundraising organisations</li>
                    <li>Statutory corporations</li>
                    <li>Municipal Councils</li>
                    <li>Industrial operations or trade</li>
                </ul>

                <h2 style="font-weight:bold">Can apply for special purposes</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Carrying out necessary work / business activity</li>
                    <li>Public Entertainment</li>
                    <li>Religious or cultural purposes</li>
                </ul>

                <h2> Activities can do</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Welding, cutting and/or grinding</li>
                    <li>Heating and spreading of bitumen and like substances</li>
                    <li>Blow lamps or gas torches</li>
                    <li>Safety fuses in blasting operations</li>
                    <li>Emergency flares at civil and military aerodromes</li>
                    <li>Flares at a petroleum fractionation plant, a gas plant or any plant of a like nature</li>
                    <li>Industrial heat testing</li>
                    <li>Bee keeping - using bee smokers</li>
                    <li>Catering - use of fire in the open air (applicant must hold a Temporary Food Premises / Stall permit from the relevant Municipal Health Officer)</li>
                    <li>Fireworks and other uses of fire for public entertainment (applicant must hold a Pryotechnical License)</li>
                    <li>Sawmill waste and refuse burners</li>
                    <li>Use of LPG burners for Hot Air Ballooning (applicant must be a commercial operator).</li>
                </ul>


                <h2><strong>Apply</strong></h2>

                <form target="_blank" action="@Url.Action("Schedule40","Home")">
